bc-duplicate (1.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * chore(version): derive CLI version string from meson.project_version()
    via -DBC_DUPLICATE_VERSION_STRING, same pattern as bc-count/bc-hash/
    bc-hrtl/bc-seek. Fix: --version used to report \"1.0.0\" even after
    the 1.1.0 release because the value was hardcoded in cli_spec.c.
  * chore(meson): declare minimum bc-* library versions.
  * chore(debian): Build-Depends bumped in sync (bc-core >= 1.3.0,
    bc-allocators >= 1.2.0).
  * chore(cppcheck): suppress unusedFunction for bench helpers in
    src/bench/**.
  * No behaviour change beyond the --version fix.

